        @{b}Major Rakal's Romulan Review #1@{ub}

Aefvadh (be welcome) to the first of Major Rakal's Romulan Reviews. Part
"card of the day," part "deck of the week," and part strategy guide, my
reviews will cover individual cards, effective combos, deck ideas, mission
selection, and general strategy, and will have a decidedly "green"
slant--as in green-blooded and green-bordered. Yes, this series will focus
on the forgotten affiliation, our friends the Romulans. Using my own
ranking system, which considers supply and demand of skills within each
affiliation, I'll cover not only Romulan but also non-aligned personnel,
examining their relative usefulness in augmenting decks of different
affiliations and recommending "Best Bets" for Rommie decks. The same for
ships.

But don't worry, there will be plenty of interest to the Klingons and Feds
as well. For missions, I'll look at point/cost ratios, and how they vary
between affiliations for multi-color ones. For dilemmas, artifacts, events,
and interrupts, I'll compare the value of a card *to* each affiliation, and
where appropriate, its value used *against* each affiliation.

For my first review, I've selected one of the new QC Romulans, IMO the Most
Valuable Personnel in a green deck right now. No, it's *not* Sirol, though
he's close. The honors go to...


    @{b}TARIS@{ub}

    Rare Romulan personnel

    Integrity 6, Cunning 8, Strength 7, Command star

    OFFICER: Archaeology, MEDICAL, Music, Transporter Skill

@{i}"Female subcommander. Captain of the Warbird Haakona. Investigated the
Federation incursion of the Neutral Zone in the vicinity of Iconia."@{ui}


She's about 2/3 of a Jean-Luc Picard. And for the Romulans, that's saying a
*lot.* She has OFFICER, Archaeology, and Music in common with the good
Captain. Navigation is replaced by Transporter Skill, likely to prove quite
valuable to nullify Anti-Matter Pods, even if you never need it against
beaming interferences. No Honor, but no Treachery either, so she can get an
Integrity boost from D'Tan from a comfortable 6 to a highly-respectable 7.
No Diplomacy or Leadership, either; but both are common enough amongst
other Romulans, and Leadership is largely redundant to an OFFICER anyway.

And these lacks are more than compensated for by her MEDICAL skill
(second-listed, so immune to Tsiolkovsky Infection and Rascals). Finally, a
Romulan doctor with other useful skills and decent stats! Until now we've
had to get by with Takket (Exobiology, OK but that's all) and Vekor
(slightly more useful with SCIENCE, Navigation, and almost useless
Geology), the holographic Jera being virtually useless to the
holodeck-deficient Romulans. Both are Firestorm and Thought Fire fuel
without Lower Decks and D'Tan, as well as Hunter Gangs bait; Taris is
immune to all three.

And while she helps run the Genetronic Replicator (which she could do alone
with a Medical Kit) and get you by so many planet dilemmas, she also makes
a new cornerstone of the popular Romulan Archaeology deck. With the new
Plague Planet mission you can do a six-planet deck with Archaeology at
every one.

But there's more. Romulans can now get a piece of the Ressikan Flute, which
until now might as well have had a blue border. Add Galen (who also
complements the Archaeology deck nicely) and maybe Amarie. Heck, Data's
Body if you can get the head to go with it. Stir well. 10-20 points, *and*
it keeps your Fed opponent from playing *his* Flute (not duplicatable).

Want more? A big boost toward getting past Matriarchal Society for the
predominantly male Romulans. With the same stats (+1 Strength) as Ocett and
duplicating her OFFICER + Archaeology, Taris will probably displace her
from a lot of decks where she was almost a necessity to augment the one
useful universal and 3 unique females.

And finally, one "skill" dictated not by Taris' card but by the Haakona's
lore "Subcommander Taris' warbird," deemed close enough by Decipher to
qualify her for Captain's Log benefits.

And this card has a *green* border??

The Major's Combos:

- Taris + Haakona + Captain's Log.  8-12-11
- The above + Major Rakal + Roga Danar + Ira Graves + Kurlan Naiskos.
  24-36-33. Go get an outpost. Throw in Plasmadyne Relay + Bynars and anything
  bigger than a Scout Ship, and you can take out a Borg Ship.
- Taris + Toreth + Mirasta Yale. Just for the heck of it.

Jolan tru,

Major Rakal
Tal Shiar
