@Node MRRR8 "STCCG.guide/Major Rakal's Romulan Review/Telak"
@TOC "STCCG:romreview.guide/MRRR"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}Major Rakal's Romulan Review@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Major Rakal's Romulan Review #8@{ub}


Aefvadh! While we're on the subject of personnel, how about that new
Security fella,


    @{b}TELAK@{ub}

"Male bodyguard of Sela. Stationed on Romulus. Lieutenant operative in
the Tal Shiar's new Android Research section."

Uncommon Romulan Personnel
Integrity 5, Cunning 6, Strength 9, Staff star
SECURITY: Treachery, Tal Shiar, Cybernetics

Our first unique Romulan SECURITY. Though one point less Cunning than
his universal comrades Jaron and Taul, he makes up for it with that
critical extra Integrity point that lets him escape Firestorms, and the
even Cunning protects him from Hunter Gangs. He's still vulnerable to
Thought Fire unless you augment his Cunning with a PADD or Yellow Alert
(though the latter negates his Hunter Gangs immunity).

SECURITY is a must for dilemmas (especially with the new Security
Precautions), but it's not required for missions (with the sole
exception of the 25-point Fed-Kli Hostage Situation just out in the new
2-Player Game), so you must make them do double duty through skills, not
an easy job for the Rommies. Jaron is good only for Youth decks, unless
you're fond of the 20-point Relief Mission. Taul is a staple in
Archaeology decks. And that's all they're good for. Telak, on the other
hand, now provides a crucial backup Tal Shiar for the good Major, making
Quash Conspiracy less risky (not to mention possible using Uncommon
personnel), as well as helping out as a leader for Romulan-Romulan
attacks. Cybernetics (the only other source of which, for Romulans, is
Ira Graves) will let you report Soong-type Androids, with their
selectable classification, "for free". So although his skills are only
good for one mission requirement, they're also useful in other ways.

Bottom line: no Roga Danar, but a lot more useful than the other Rommie
SECURITY, and only Uncommon.

The Major's Combos:

- Telak + Major Rakal + Quash Conspiracy

Jolan tru,

Major Rakal
Tal Shiar
