        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}Major Rakal's Romulan Review@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Major Rakal's Romulan Review #14@{ub}


Aefvadh! Here's a card I've had several requests for, so I guess it's
time to do it. Though it's green-bordered, it also has a tinge of blue,
and I seldom build a deck without it. That's right, none other
than...NO, not Stefan DeSeve! None other than our very own...


    @{b}MAJOR RAKAL@{ub}

    Rare Romulan/Federation (Dual-Affiliation) Personnel

    Integrity 4, Cunning 8, Strength 4, Command star, AU icon

    V.I.P.: Romulan: Tal Shiar, Empathy, Treachery
            Federation: Empathy, Diplomacy, INTEGRITY +4, CUNNING -1

@{i}"Physically altered, Deanna Troi was coerced to completely assume the
identity of a Tal Shiar major in the 2369 M'ret defection plot."@{ui} [The
name "Deanna Troi" is *not* in boldface, though errata will soon be
issued stating that it should be, indicating Rakal and Troi are the same
persona.]

This first dual-affiliation personnel was a great breakthrough for the
Romulans, providing by far the most valuable personnel available to the
Empire prior to the release of Taris and Sirol. Look at her advantages:

- Empathy. Rommies no longer had to rely on a single available Empath,
Devinoni Ral, unique and therefore unplayable in duplicate, to do the 40
point New Contact mission. The release of AU also made Empathy a
critical skill for countering Thought Fire (devastating to Romulans) and
Cardassian Trap. With Maques, she even provides hope of curing Frame of
Mind. And it's her *second* listed skill, untouchable by Rascals or
Tsiolkovsky Infection. Her Empathy alone makes her a virtual necessity
in any Romulan deck. But she has plenty more to recommend her.
- Treachery. Never can have enough of this for your basic Romulan
Treachery deck.
- Tal Shiar. A 40-point mission (Quash Conspiracy) she can complete on
her own. Just keep the Major on a handy Scout or Science Vessel
(preferably upline from the mission to avoid Borg Ship surprises) while
your basic crew takes out the dilemmas. Then when they are unable to
complete the mission, their attempt ends, move in the Major, and score
40. In addition, she can now serve as a battle leader if you have no
other, and allow you to attack a Romulan opponent.
- Female. With only 6 other Romulan females, two of which (Jera and
Selok) are virtually useless, she's real handy for those Matriarchal
Societies.
- AU Icon. Put her on a Cryosatellite, use her to staff the Decius,
complete Fissure Research.
- VIP Classification. A great backup VIP for Diplomatic Conference, as
you can use her for whichever affiliation you didn't already draw.
- Even CUNNING. Immune to Hunter Gangs.
- Dual Affiliation. She justifies seeding of an extra (Neutral) outpost
for her potential Federation affiliation, and allows you to "espionage"
Federation mission with the backup of non-aligned support personnel.

Her only Romulan disadvantage is her Integrity of 4, leaving her
vulnerable to Firestorms with no help available from D'Tan or Lower
Decks.

What about (heresy!) Federation decks? Well, in blue mode our Major is
just a clone of Deanna Troi, with two exceptions: her classification is
VIP instead of OFFICER (no big loss), and she has an AU icon. Which
makes her an nice replacement for her alter ego, as the advantages
listed above for these two features apply just as well to Federation
use, including staffing for the AU-hungry Future Enterprise. And her
dual affiliation again allows seeding of a Neutral Outpost, this time
for potential green-ness, not to mention the possibility of otherwise
impossible "espionage" of Romulan missions with non-aligned support
crew!

All in all, great for both affiliations, but with far more advantages
accruing to the Romulans. Don't leave the Outpost without her.

The Major's Combos:

- Major Rakal + any of my decks

Jolan tru,

Major Rakal
Tal Shiar

