@TOC "STCCG:romreview.guide/MRRR"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}Major Rakal's Romulan Review@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Major Rakal's Romulan Review #30@{ub}


Aefvadh! They promised us something for the Romulans in Fajo, and here
she is...


    @{b}TALLERA@{ub}

    Romulan/Federation/Non-aligned Personnel, unique,
    Limited Edition, (Fajo Collection)

    Integrity 3, Cunning 7, Strength 7, Command Star

SECURITY: Computer Skill, SCIENCE, Mindmeld, Leadership, Treachery
Does not work with [Federation] affiliation personnel.

@{i}"Female Romulan mercenary. In reality a physically altered Vulcan
isolationist seeking the Stone of Gol."@{ui}


Not *quite* the "six-skilled Romulan" that we've been hearing persistent
rumors of, but she *is* the first triple-affiliation personnel (granting
that "affiliation" is a misnomer for Non-aligned, as with Garak). Her
Non-aligned icon lets her work with the Klingons, as well as the
upcoming Cardassians, or anyone else--except of course the Feds.

Now, what good is her Federation icon, if she can't work with Feds?
Well, note that her restriction box reads just a little bit different
than those of Galen or Nick Locarno; while they won't work with
Federation *affiliation*, Tallera won't work with Federation affiliation
*personnel*. That means that, like Major Rakal, she could fly a
Federation ship, and more important, attempt a Federation mission, with
appropriate NA support crew. Of course, she also enables the seeding of
a second outpost like the other dual-affiliates.

With Tallera, the Romulans add another dual-classification personnel to
the fold. The combination of SECURITY and SCIENCE is an odd one, but
might prove useful: many dilemmas require either MEDICAL + SCIENCE or
MEDICAL + SECURITY to pass, with Barclay's Protomorphosis Disease
requiring all three. So a single MEDICAL with Tallera can pass a
considerable number of killer dilemmas. And she enables a couple of
unique Kurlan Naiskos combos (see below).

Her other skills, for the most part, are nothing spectacular. Computer
Skill and Treachery are common enough among Romulans and Non-aligned
(though to be sure they are required by plenty of Romulan missions), and
Leadership is mainly useful in allowing her to lead in battle. But her
remaining skill is so far unique outside of the blue cards. Yes, Tallera
finally brings "Mindmeld for the rest of us." Now I'll have to work up a
Mindmeld strategy for the Romulans, something I've never been able to
even consider before. (Let's see, she can gain Treachery from almost any
Rommie...) And oh, yes, she overcomes Interphasic Plasma Creatures, too.

Her attributes, unfortunately, are pretty lackluster. She's a sitting
duck for Firestorm, Thought Fire, and Hunter Gangs, and a STRENGTH of 7
isn't great for a Romulan. (An interesting side note: the Vulcan Stone
of Gol would kill Tallera, Narik, and Vekor (all CUNNING 7), while
sparing Galen (8).)

Ironically, her NA icon actually makes her more useful to the Klingons
than to the Romulans. They gain access to Mindmeld, and now have someone
they can use to "espionage" both Federation and Romulan missions, while
Tallera adds nothing there that the Romulans don't already have. And the
Klingons have more need for Treachery and Computer Skill than do the
Rommies.

The Major's Combos:

- Tallera + Taris + Major Rakal + Kareen Brianon + Decius + Kurlan
Naiskos

- Tallera + Ja'rod + Kurn + K'chiQ (with MEDICAL skill) + IKC Feh'lhr +
Kurlan Naiskos

- Tallera + Galen + Baran + Narik + Vekor + Mercenary Ship (just for the
heck of it; but I count at least 11 missions this team could do, though
a couple will need a Mindmeld, and several more if you add Roga Danar)

